STEP ONE - Plan Your Model: Select all of the properties and behaviors needed for your model.

Your medical delivery truck need to maintain a constant, slow velocity while passing a farm. In this task, you will analyze the time it takes to pass the farm.
STEP ONE - Plan Your Model: Select all of the properties and behaviors needed for your model in the Physics tab.
STEP TWO - Build Your Model (go back to Scripts tab) 1.) Set the values for all of the needed, selected properties under the [When Green Flag Clicked] block.
Define the simulation step of your simulation model to program your truck to move a constant velocity of 0.6m/s (the speed limit while passing the farm). Use the cones to support you in analyzing how much time it takes to travel the distance of the farm (to the intersecting dirt road at the noted constant velocity. Now run an experiment noting the distance traveled at different points in time starting from cone 1. Use the values you generate from your simulation model to draw a distance versus time graph. What is the nature of this plot? What corresponds to the velocity of the vehicle in this plot? Why is generating a graph useful?
